早在2008年时，已经4度连任的宾夕法尼亚州共和党联邦参议员阿伦·斯佩克特就明确表示有意再度竞选连任<ref>{{Cite news | title = Arlen unfazed by Specter of run vs. Chris Matthews | publisher = Associated Press | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121025132617/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/arlen-unfazed-specter-run-chris-matthews-article-1.357819 | date = 2008-11-30 | accessdate = 2015-09-30 | archivedate = 2012-10-25 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/arlen-unfazed-specter-run-chris-matthews-article-1.357819 }}</ref>。2004年参议员选举期间，斯佩克特面临保守派[[帕特·图米|帕特·图米]]的强烈挑战，最终虽赢得初选，但优势非常微弱，这次图米的来势更加猛烈<ref name="Connolly0409">{{Cite news | last = Connolly | first = Katie | title = Specter Will Not Run as an Independent | work = Newsweek | date = 2009-04-09 | accessdate = 2015-09-30 | archivedate = 2010-12-03 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20101203022600/http://www.newsweek.com/blogs/the-gaggle/2009/04/09/specter-will-not-run-as-an-independent.html | url = http://www.newsweek.com/specter-will-not-run-independent-211248 | deadurl = no }}</ref><ref name="PburgBiz">{{cite news | title = Arlen Specter trailing in new Quinnipiac poll | work = Pittsburgh Business Times | date = 2009-03-25 | url = http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/stories/2009/03/23/daily25.html | accessdate = 2014-04-23 | archivedate = 2014-04-23 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140423225821/http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/stories/2009/03/23/daily25.html }}</ref>，特别是[[宾夕法尼亚州共和党委员会|宾夕法尼亚州共和党]]的保守派系还发誓一定要让斯佩克特在即将到来的初选中败兴而归<ref>{{cite news |last=Vecsey |first=Laura |title=Specter vote angers Republicans |work=The Patriot-News |url=http://www.pennlive.com/statehouse/patriotnews/index.ssf?/base/news/1234497302147690.xml&coll=1 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120223114715/http://www.pennlive.com/statehouse/patriotnews/index.ssf?%2Fbase%2Fnews%2F1234497302147690.xml&coll=1 |date=2009-02-13 |accessdate=2015-09-30 |archivedate=2012-02-23 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。包括[[美国副总统|副总统]][[乔·拜登|乔·拜登]]、州长伦德尔在内的部分知名民主党人公开表示，只要斯佩克特转投民主党，他们愿在筹款方面助一臂之力，以此鼓励他转换党派<ref name="Connolly0409" />。2009年3月，[[昆尼皮亚克大学民意调查中心|昆尼皮亚克大学民意调查中心]]经民调发现，斯佩克特在共和党初选选民中的支持率仅有27%，远不及图米的41%，这很大程度上是因为选民对斯佩克特支持奥巴马总统提出的《[[2009年美国复苏与再投资法案|2009年美国复苏与再投资法案]]》感到忧虑<ref name="PburgBiz" /><ref name="Montopoli0325">{{cite news | last = Montopoli | first = Brian | title = Specter In Trouble In Pennsylvania | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121102232353/http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-503544_162-4892947-503544.html | publisher = CBS News | date = 2009-03-25 | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/specter-in-trouble-in-pennsylvania/ | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2015-09-30 | archivedate = 2012-11-02 }}</ref>。随着宾夕法尼亚州初选日期逐渐逼近，民调结果显示斯佩克特也无法得到温和派和民主党选民的支持<ref name="Montopoli0325" />。昆尼皮亚克大学民意调查中心副主任克莱·理查兹（{{lang|en|Clay F. Richards}}）针对民调结果表示：“宾夕法尼亚州的共和党人对参议员斯佩克特投票支持贝拉克·奥巴马总统经济刺激政策和所谓猪肉桶支出方案的做法是如此不满，为此甚至准备把票投给他们几乎一无所知的前[[美国众议院|联邦众议员]]”<ref name="PburgBiz" /><ref name="Montopoli0325" />。

2009年3月，《[[国会山报|国会山报]]》在报道中引述斯佩克特的话，称他正考虑退出共和党，以独立候选人身份争取连任<ref>{{Cite news | last = Vecsey | first = Laura | title = Arlen Specter: I am a Republican | work = The Patriot-News | date = 2009-03-18 | url = http://www.pennlive.com/midstate/index.ssf/2009/03/specter_i_am_a_republican.html | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120404114425/http://www.pennlive.com/midstate/index.ssf/2009/03/specter_i_am_a_republican.html | archivedate = 2012-04-04 | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2015-09-30 }}</ref>。但是，斯佩克特很快又否认了这一说法<ref name="Connolly0409" />，他于3月18日宣布：“为了消除任何疑虑，（我在此宣布：）我是共和党人，我也会在2010年以共和党人身份作为共和党候选人竞选连任”<ref>{{Cite news | last = Fitzgerald | first = Thomas | date = 2009-03-19 | work = The Philadelphia Inquirer | title = Specter staying on Republican ticket | page = B07}}</ref>。但到了2009年4月28日，斯佩克特又宣布自己决定脱离共和党，转投民主党，因为他对共和党朝日趋保守的方向前进感到不满，还发现自己的个人哲学与民主党更加接近。虽然斯佩克特表示自己主要是因原则而转换党派，但他承认赢得共和党初选的希望渺茫也是他做此决定的原因之一：“我已经前往州内各地，调查宾夕法尼亚州共和党人的情绪，了解民调结果，发现赢得共和党初选的前景非常黯淡。”<ref name="CNN0428">{{cite news | last1 = Hornick | first1 = Ed | last2 = Walsh | first2 = Deirdre | title = Longtime GOP Sen. Arlen Specter becomes Democrat | work = CNN | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150508151328/http://edition.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/04/28/specter.party.switch/index.html | date = 2009-04-28 | url = http://edition.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/04/28/specter.party.switch/index.html | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2015-09-30 | archivedate = 2015-05-08 }}</ref><ref name="Montopoli0428">{{cite news | last = Montopoli | first = Brian | title = Sen. Arlen Specter To Become A Democrat | publisher = CBS News | date = 2009-04-28 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121102234031/http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-503544_162-4974413-503544.html | deadurl = no | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/sen-arlen-specter-to-become-a-democrat/ | accessdate = 2015-09-30 | archivedate = 2012-11-02 }}</ref>

联邦参议院多数党领袖[[哈里·瑞德|哈里·瑞德]]在斯佩克特转换党派前向他承诺，即便加入民主党，斯佩克特仍然可以保留他在参议院的资历<ref name="Kane0506">{{cite news |last=Kane |first=Paul |title=Party Switch Costs Specter His Seniority on Senate Committees |work=The Washington Post |accessdate=2015-09-30 |date=2009-05-06 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130209025139/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/05/05/AR2009050504344.html |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/05/05/AR2009050504344.html |archivedate=2013-02-09 |deadurl=no }}</ref><ref name="OToole0507">{{cite news | last = O'Toole | first = James | title = Specter's loss of tenure could foil party alliance swap | work = Pittsburgh Post-Gazette | date = 2009-05-07 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121023082215/http://www.post-gazette.com/stories/news/politics-national/specters-loss-of-tenure-could-foil-party-alliance-swap-341054/ | accessdate = 2015-09-30 | archivedate = 2012-10-23 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.post-gazette.com/nation/2009/05/07/Specter-s-loss-of-tenure-could-foil-party-alliance-swap/stories/200905070326 }}</ref>。这一安排令部分民主党参议员感到不快<ref>{{cite news | last = Baier | first = Bret | title = Senate Democrats Balk at Specter Deal | publisher = Fox News | date = 2009-04-30 | accessdate = 2015-09-30 | archivedate = 2012-11-03 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121103222744/http://www.foxnews.com/on-air/special-report/2009/04/30/senate-democrats-balk-specter-deal | url = http://www.foxnews.com/on-air/special-report/2009/04/30/senate-democrats-balk-specter-deal | deadurl = yes }}</ref>，5月3日，联邦参议院经投票决定不顾瑞德的承诺剥夺斯佩克特的资历。这令斯佩克特突然沦落为参议院中最资浅的民主党议员，导致他在立法方面的影响力严重受限<ref name="Kane0506" /><ref name="OToole0507" />。不过，还是有许多民主党要人赞赏斯佩克特的决定，这其中包括瑞德和奥巴马总统，后者还承诺向斯佩克特的竞选提供支持。共和党则对斯佩克特加以谴责，批评他为了自己的政治前程背叛原则和党派。<ref name="CNN0428" /><ref name="Montopoli0428" />[[共和党全国委员会|共和党全国委员会]]主席[[迈克尔·斯蒂尔|迈克尔·斯蒂尔]]（{{lang|en|Michael Steele}}）称，斯派克特向党派“[[竖中指|竖起中指]]”，他完全是因为自知会输掉选举才做出这一决定<ref name="CNN0428" />。全国共和党参议院主席，联邦参议员[[约翰·康宁|约翰·康宁]]曾是斯佩克特的支持者，他也指责这一决定“代表政治上明哲保身的新高度”<ref name="Montopoli0428" />。斯佩克特辩称，共和党已经同当年[[罗纳德·里根|罗纳德·里根]]总统的设想偏离太远，他还称，“我还不准备让宾夕法尼亚州共和党初选的选民来对我29个年头的联邦参议院纪录指手划脚”<ref name="Montopoli0428" />。

=== 乔·谢斯塔克宣布参选 ===
2008年12月，前[[美国海军|美国海军]]上将、正担任联邦众议员（第2个任期）的[[乔·谢斯塔克|乔·谢斯塔克]]开始同家人商议是否出马竞争民主党联邦参议员提名<ref>{{cite news | last = Barnes | first = Tom | title = Poll: Specter's lead over GOP challenger narrows | accessdate = 2015-09-30 | work = Pittsburgh Post-Gazette | date = 2009-05-29 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090603195649/http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/09149/973544-178.stm | url = http://www.post-gazette.com/politics-state/2009/05/29/Poll-Specter-s-lead-over-GOP-challenger-narrows/stories/200905290200 | archivedate = 2009-06-03 }}</ref>。[[民主党参议员竞选委员会|民主党参议员竞选委员会]]主席、联邦参议员[[罗伯特·曼南德兹|罗伯特·曼南德兹]]于2009年4月主动联系谢斯塔克，希望他能参选，但谢斯塔克这时表示自己对此不是很有意向<ref name="PI0723">{{cite news | last = Cook | first = Bonnie L. | title = Sestak's Senate candidacy is not official yet | work = The Philadelphia Inquirer | date = 2009-07-23 | page = B02}}</ref><ref name="Rotenberg0124">{{cite news | last = Rotenberg | first = Carl | title = Trying to make Pa. 'all it should be' | work = The Times Herald | date = 2010-01-24}}</ref>。2009年4月中旬，开始有媒体报道猜测谢斯塔克的参选可能<ref>{{cite news | title = Specter's Hot Seat | publisher = WPXI | date = 2009-04-17 | archivedate = 2012-08-19 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120819102140/http://www.wpxi.com/news/news/specters-hot-seat/nGYNd/ | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.wpxi.com/news/news/specters-hot-seat/nGYNd/ | accessdate = 2015-09-30 }}</ref>，这种猜测的热度还在斯佩克特转换党派当天增强。虽然大部分民主党人都对长年担任参议员的斯佩克特表示欢迎，但谢斯塔克却发表声明谴责斯佩克特的决定，称这不过是投机取巧的举动，在做出这样的决定前，斯佩克特应当征求宾夕法尼亚州人民的意见，而不是去和参议院民主党领袖以及首都的政治机构商议<ref name="Pergram0429">{{cite news | last1 = Berger | first1 = Judson | last2 = Pergram | first2 = Chad | title = Specter Could Face Challengers in Democratic Primary | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121026062117/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/04/29/specter-face-challengers-democratic-primary/ | archivedate = 2012-10-26 | deadurl = yes | publisher = Fox News | accessdate = 2015-09-30 | date = 2010-04-29 | url = http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/04/29/specter-face-challengers-democratic-primary/ }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | last = Hockensmith | first = Dustin | title = Joe Sestak leans toward run against Arlen Specter | work = The Patriot-News | date = 2009-05-16 | url = http://www.pennlive.com/midstate/index.ssf/2009/05/joe_sestak_leans_towards_run_a.html | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120404114429/http://www.pennlive.com/midstate/index.ssf/2009/05/joe_sestak_leans_towards_run_a.html | accessdate = 2015-09-30 | archivedate = 2012-04-04 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。曼南德兹再次联系谢斯塔克，请他不要再和斯佩克特作对，但谢斯塔克拒绝让步<ref name="Rotenberg0124" />。谢斯塔克之后在接受[[福克斯新闻频道|福克斯新闻]]采访时坚称，自己尚未就是否参选做出决定，但他也拒绝马上表态支持斯派克特，表示自己还需观望一阵<ref name="Pergram0429" />。5月3日，谢斯塔克走上{{lang|en|[[CNN|CNN]]}}的《[[杰克·塔柏国情咨文|约翰·金国情咨文]]》（{{lang|en|''State of the Union with John King''}}）栏目，在节目中对斯派克特是否能算作真正的民主党人提出质疑，他还称：“我觉得阿伦需要告诉我们的不是竞选中的哪个对手有多厉害……我想知道的是，他到底是为了什么而参选？”<ref>{{cite episode | title = The Last Word: Interview with Joe Sestak | url = http://edition.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0905/03/sotu.04.html | series = State of the Union with John King | credits = King, John | network = CNN | city = New York City | airdate = 2009-05-03 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150224002255/http://edition.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0905/03/sotu.04.html | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2015-02-24 | access-date = 2015-09-30 }}</ref>

{{Quote box |quoted=true |bgcolor=#FFFFF0 |salign=center |width=225px |align=right | quote  = 我竞选宾夕法尼亚州下任联邦参议员，因为我决心给子孙后代留下更加美好的世界。这需要领导人承诺以诚实守信为原则，承担责任、努力工作。我们送去华盛顿的人要代表你、为你着想，如果没有做到，他们就必须对此负责。 | source = 乔·谢斯塔克宣布参选<ref name="Wereschagin0804">{{cite news | last = Wereschagin | first = Mike | title = Specter to face primary challenge from Rep. Joe Sestak | work = Pittsburgh Tribune-Review | date = 2009-08-04 | url = http://triblive.com//x/pittsburghtrib/news/regional/s_636696.html | accessdate = 2015-10-01 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150930165250/http://triblive.com//x/pittsburghtrib/news/regional/s_636696.html | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2015-09-30 }}</ref>。}}

之后的几个月里，谢斯塔克都没有对参选与否做出最后决定。5月4日，他和[[服务业雇员国际工会|服务业雇员国际工会]]主席[[安迪·斯特恩|安迪·斯特恩]]（{{lang|en|Andy Stern}}）碰头，引起外界猜测他正为竞选争取劳工支持<ref>{{cite news | last = Kraushaar | first = Josh | title = After Specter Switch: Buyer's Remorse? | publisher = CBS News | date = 2009-05-04 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121102234038/http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2009/05/04/politics/politico/main4991002.shtml | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/after-specter-switch-buyers-remorse/ | accessdate = 2015-10-01 | archivedate = 2012-11-02 }}</ref>。在此期间，[[美国国家宪法中心|美国国家宪法中心]]前主席[[乔·托赛拉|乔·托赛拉]]（{{lang|en|Joe Torsella}}）已经计划加入对民主党提名的竞争，并且一度宣布斯佩克特调换党派之举不会影响自己参选的决定<ref>{{cite news | archivedate = 2009-05-05 | archiveurl = https://archive.is/20090505181732/http://www.montgomerynews.com/articles/2009/04/30/glenside_news_globe_times_chronicle/news/doc49f93bcaea31c796158315.txt | last1 = Malinowski | first1 = Nick | last2 = Finarelli | first2 = Linda | title = Torsella still committed to run for Senate | work = Springfield Sun | date = 2009-04-30 | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.montgomerynews.com/articles/2009/04/30/glenside_news_globe_times_chronicle/news/doc49f93bcaea31c796158315.txt | accessdate = 2015-10-01 }}</ref>。但到了5月14日，托赛拉又宣布退出竞争，理由是斯佩克特的决定已经改变了政治格局，他不希望致身于这样一场“可能会掺杂各种相互揭短、个人攻击，更多关注于斯佩克特参议员的过去而不是我们共同未来”的竞选<ref>{{cite news | last = Condon | first = Stephanie | title = Specter's Primary Challenger Drops Out | publisher = CBS News | date = 2009-05-15 | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/specters-primary-challenger-drops-out/ | accessdate = 2015-10-01 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121102234053/http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-503544_162-5016249-503544.html | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2012-11-02 }}</ref>。另据报道，州长伦德尔亲自向托赛拉施压，要求他退出竞争，让斯佩克特可以在没有对手的情况下参选，但托赛拉手下的工作人员否认这一说法<ref name="Pergram0429" />。托赛拉退出后，谢斯塔克还是打算参选，并开始争取民主党中类似[[渐进改革竞选委员会|渐进改革竞选委员会]]这样更偏向自由主义的派系支持，还开始为“选秀谢斯塔克”竞选活动筹资<ref>{{cite news | last = Erdley | first = Debra | title = Primary may yet trip up Specter | work = Pittsburgh Tribune-Review | accessdate = 2015-10-01 | date = 2009-05-12 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151001072728/http://triblive.com//x/pittsburghtrib/news/regional/s_624663.html#axzz3nF37NGd7 | archivedate = 2015-10-01 | url = http://triblive.com//x/pittsburghtrib/news/regional/s_624663.html#axzz3nF37NGd7 }}</ref>。谢斯塔克走遍[[宾夕法尼亚州行政区划|宾夕法尼亚州全部67个县]]，与多位党派领导人会晤并对包括就业、经验和医疗保险在内的众多议题交换意见，这些经历进一步鼓励了他参选的信心<ref name="PI0723" />。谢斯塔克表示，许多党派领导人在同他交流的过程中对国家的走向表示严重关切，虽然知名度不足还是他面临的严重问题，但在谢斯塔克看来，许多接触过的人都表示愿意支持他<ref>{{cite news | last = Rose | first = Alex | title = Sestak says state residents voiced displeasure on tour | work = Delaware County Daily Times | date = 2009-07-23 | accessdate = 2015-10-01 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120329202406/http://www.delcotimes.com/articles/2009/07/23/news/doc4a67d6c8d6550938072695.txt | url = http://www.delcotimes.com/general-news/20090723/sestak-says-state-residents-voiced-displeasure-on-tour | archivedate = 2012-03-29 }}</ref>。

5月27日，政治新闻网站[[谈话要点备忘录|谈话要点备忘录]]（{{lang|en|Talking Points Memo}}，简称{{lang|en|TPM}}）发布谢斯塔克致其他候选人的亲笔信，宣布他有意竞选参议员。谢斯塔克在面对媒体时没有否认这封信的真实性，但表示自己打算在正式决定前再和家人商议。<ref>{{cite news | last = Logue | first = Timothy | title = 'I intend to run for the U.S. Senate' | work = The Times Herald | date = 2009-05-29}}</ref>谢斯塔克还向媒体透露，他知道奥巴马总统希望他不要参选同斯佩克特竞争，但他觉得这应该由宾夕法尼亚州的选民而非总统来决定<ref>{{cite news | title = Sestak: I Will Reject Obama Request to Step Aside in Pennsylvania Senate Race | publisher = Fox News | date = 2009-06-02 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121026062210/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/06/02/sestak-reject-obama-request-step-aside-pennsylvania-senate-race/ | accessdate = 2015-10-01 | archivedate = 2012-10-26 | url = http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/06/02/sestak-reject-obama-request-step-aside-pennsylvania-senate-race/ }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = Martin | first = Jonathan | title = Two Dems Plan Senate Primary Challenges | publisher = CBS News | date = 2009-06-15 | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/two-dems-plan-senate-primary-challenges/ | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121102234134/http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2009/06/14/politics/politico/main5088130.shtml | accessdate = 2015-10-01 | archivedate = 2012-11-02 }}</ref>。伦德尔州长也曾公开建议谢斯塔克不要参选，觉得这不但会伤及谢斯塔克的政治前程，还会导致民主党失去谢斯塔克在联邦众议院的议席，甚至降低斯佩克特在普选中的胜算<ref>{{cite news | last = Thrush | first = Glenn | title = Rendell wants Sestak to ditch Senate bid | work = Politico | date = 2009-07-20 | accessdate = 2015-10-01 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150930125236/http://www.politico.com/blogs/on-congress/2009/07/rendell-wants-sestak-to-ditch-senate-bid-020008 | archivedate = 2015-09-30 | url = http://www.politico.com/blogs/on-congress/2009/07/rendell-wants-sestak-to-ditch-senate-bid-020008 }}</ref>。尽管如此，谢斯塔克还是于2009年8月4日在故乡[[特拉华县_(宾夕法尼亚州)|特拉华县]]的[[对外战争退伍军人|对外战争退伍军人]]大堂前发表演出，正式宣布加入民主党提名的竞争<ref name="Wereschagin0804" />。不久，图米发表声明，表示欢迎谢斯塔克加入竞选，称他是“始终如一的自由派，真心相信自己的价值观”，与之相比，他对斯佩克特的评价就不堪得多，称后者是“职业性的政治投机主义者，除了自己的连任外没有任何信念”<ref name="Dale0805">{{cite news | title = Sestak will try to unseat Specter | last = Dale | first = Mary Claire | work = Bucks County Courier Times | date = 2009-08-05 | page = A1}}</ref>。

