谢斯塔克在5月18日的初选中以53.8%的得票率获胜，一共得到56万8563票，斯佩克特则为48万7217票，占选票总数的46.2%<ref name="Results" />。这一结果也给斯佩克特近30年的联邦参议员生涯划上句点，比宾夕法尼亚州历史上其他任何联邦参议员的在职时间都要长<ref name="McCormick0518" /><ref name="Feldmann0519" />。谢斯塔克随后宣布：“民主就应该是这样：由人民战胜固有机制。对于希望变革的人们来说，这一结果毫不意外。”斯佩克特承认败选并表示：“能够为宾夕法尼亚州人民效劳是莫大的荣幸。能够进入联邦参议院（也）是莫大的荣幸。”<ref name="McCormick0518" />多位评论员指出，这次选举结果标志着选民对两个主要政党的既有机制都不满意，还表明在这个政治时代，政界要人的支持对选民影响不大<ref name="Feldmann0519">{{cite news | last = Feldmann | first = Linda | title = Arlen Specter out, Rand Paul advances, Blanche Lincoln fights on | work = The Christian Science Monitor | url = http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0519/Arlen-Specter-out-Rand-Paul-advances-Blanche-Lincoln-fights-on | date = 2010-05-19 | accessdate = 2015-10-03 | archivedate = 2015-09-25 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150925010729/http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0519/Arlen-Specter-out-Rand-Paul-advances-Blanche-Lincoln-fights-on }}</ref>。奥巴马在这轮竞选期间极力并公开支持斯佩克特，因此有评论认为谢斯塔克的胜利多少会令总统有些难堪<ref name="Nicholas0915" /><ref name="Feldmann0519" />。多家新闻媒体认为，谢斯塔克在电视广告中谴责斯佩克特的投机主义行径和虚伪成效显著，有可能是他最终获胜的主要原因<ref name="Crushing" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Cillizza |first=Chris |title=The Fix - How (and why) Arlen Specter lost |work=The Washington Post |date=2010-05-19 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120722020928/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/thefix/morning-fix/1-2-3-4.html |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/thefix/morning-fix/1-2-3-4.html |accessdate=2015-10-03 |archivedate=2012-07-22 |deadurl=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = Mauriello | first = Tracie | title = Sestak bucks the odds, party regulars in U.S. Senate primary win | work = Pittsburgh Post-Gazette | date = 2010-05-19 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140311180608/http://www.post-gazette.com/news/politics-nation/2010/05/19/Sestak-bucks-the-odds-party-regulars-in-U-S-Senate-primary-win/stories/201005190180 | archivedate = 2014-03-11 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.post-gazette.com/politics-nation/2010/05/19/Sestak-bucks-the-odds-party-regulars-in-U-S-Senate-primary-win/stories/201005190180 | accessdate = 2015-10-03 }}</ref>。《华盛顿邮报》称，斯佩克特担任参议员时间之长，以及他变更党派之举，令宾夕法尼亚州的这场初选比2010年的其它任何初选关注度都要高<ref name="BalzCillizza" />。

谢斯塔克虽然取得民主党的提名，但是在参议院选举中输给共和党候选人图米，谢斯塔克以49%对51%落败，落后80,229票。<ref>{{cite web | title = 2010 General Election | date = 2010-11-02 | publisher = Pennsylvania Department of State | accessdate = 2012-03-14 | archivedate = 2012-03-14 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120314023015/http://www.electionreturns.state.pa.us/ElectionsInformation.aspx?FunctionID=13&ElectionID=39&OfficeID=2 | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.electionreturns.state.pa.us/ElectionsInformation.aspx?FunctionID=13&ElectionID=39&OfficeID=2 }}</ref><ref>{{cite  news | last1 = Fitzgerald | first = Thomas | last2 = Gammage | first2 = Jeff | last3 = Schaefer | first3 = Mari | title = Toomey beats Sestak | work = The Philadelphia Inquirer | date = 2010-11-03 | accessdate = 2015-10-03 | url = http://articles.philly.com/2010-11-03/news/24954629_1_republican-pat-toomey-exit-polls-campaign | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150930203034/http://articles.philly.com/2010-11-03/news/24954629_1_republican-pat-toomey-exit-polls-campaign | archivedate = 2015-09-30 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。

== 克林顿向谢斯塔克提出的工作邀约 ==
{{Quote box |quoted=true |bgcolor=#FFFFF0 |salign=center |width=195px |align=right | quote  = 可能白宫觉得这在政治上稀松平常，但这其中非常不同寻常的地方在于，候选人——至少也是联邦众议员——会毫不保留地承认这种提议。候选人对这种交易几乎从来都不会声张，他们也有很好的理由这么做——这是犯法的。| source = 联邦众议员达雷尔·伊萨<ref name="Sherman0310">{{cite news | last = Sherman | first = Jake | title = Darrell Issa raises questions about Joe Sestak | url = http://www.politico.com/story/2010/03/issa-raises-questions-about-sestak-034221 | accessdate = 2015-10-03 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151001094432/http://www.politico.com/story/2010/03/issa-raises-questions-about-sestak-034221 | archivedate = 2015-10-01 | deadurl = no | publisher = Politico | date = 2010-03-10 }}</ref>}}

2010年2月，谢斯塔克在接受电视采访时称，有人以奥巴马政府内的官职为筹码，要求他退出竞选。这个月18日，谢斯塔克参加费城地区地方新闻节目《拉里·凯恩：理性的声音》（{{lang|en|''Larry Kane: Voice of Reason''}}）的录制，主持人[[拉里·凯恩|拉里·凯恩]]（{{lang|en|Larry Kane}}）询问是否的确有人提出这种交易，谢斯塔克给出肯定答复，但除了说明这是个比较高阶的职务外没有其它详细解释，也没有说明自己不打算接受<ref name="Pershing0219">{{cite news |last=Pershing |first=Ben |title=Sestak alleges WH offered him a job to drop Senate bid |work=The Washington Post |date=2010-02-19 |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2010/02/sestak-alleges-wh-offered-him.html |accessdate=2015-10-02 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130205174826/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2010/02/sestak-alleges-wh-offered-him.html |archivedate=2013-02-05 |deadurl=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = Good | first = Chris | title = A Job Offer For Sestak | work = The Atlantic | date = 2010-02-22 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150930125045/http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2010/02/a-job-offer-for-sestak/36333/ | url = http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2010/02/a-job-offer-for-sestak/36333/ | accessdate = 2015-10-03 | archivedate = 2015-09-30 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。他在接下来多次面对媒体质询时都坚持原有说法，例如在接受《华盛顿邮报》采访时表示：“他们已经试图通过一些间接手段表示，如果我愿意退出，他们会以某些东西为交换。”之后他又在福克斯新闻频道上称：“昨天有人直截了当地问我，我也诚实地回答了。这里面没有别的什么隐情，我现在已经加入竞争。”<ref name="Pershing0219" />接下来的1个月里，白宫方面一直没有回答多家媒体有关谢斯塔克的说法是否属实的提问。3月16日，[[白宫新闻发言人|白宫新闻发言人]][[罗伯特·吉布斯|罗伯特·吉布斯]]表示他已对此事进行了解，结论是白宫方面同谢斯塔克之间有过的对话都“不会构成问题”。<ref name="Feldmann0316">{{cite news | last = Feldmann | first = Linda | title = Did the White House offer Joe Sestak a job? | work = The Christian Science Monitor | date = 2010-03-16 | archivedate = 2015-09-30 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150930182031/http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0316/Did-the-White-House-offer-Joe-Sestak-a-job | url = http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0316/Did-the-White-House-offer-Joe-Sestak-a-job | accessdate = 2015-10-02 | deadurl = no }}</ref>

3月，联邦众议员、[[美国众议院监督和政府改革委员会|众议院监督和政府改革委员会]]成员[[达雷尔·伊萨|达雷尔·伊萨]]致信[[白宫律师|白宫律师]][[罗伯特·鲍尔|罗伯特·鲍尔]]（{{lang|en|Robert Bauer}}），信中称如果谢斯塔克的说法属实，奥巴马政府有可能已经违反联邦法规，根据该法规，政府雇员利用手中职权干预选举属于非法行为<ref name="Sherman0310" /><ref name="Feldmann0316" />。谢斯塔克在5月18日的初选中击败斯佩克特后，这一事件再度引起关注。[[美国参议院司法委员会|参议院司法委员会]]的7名共和党议员致信[[美国司法部长|司法部长]][[埃里克·霍尔德|埃里克·霍尔德]]，要求对此事涉及的法律问题进行审查。在此期间，谢斯塔克仍然坚称事件属实，但也表示事件并不是多么严重，并为奥巴马的品格辩护。<ref>{{cite news |last=Kane |first=Paul |title=Sestak says his brother, White House met about alleged job offer |work=The Washington Post |date=2010-05-28 |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/05/27/AR2010052705245.html |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120918220831/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/05/27/AR2010052705245.html |archivedate=2012-09-18 |deadurl=no |accessdate=2015-10-03 }}</ref>5月28日，白宫正式回应指控，承认[[白宫新闻办公厅主任|白宫新闻办公厅主任]][[拉姆·伊曼纽尔|拉姆·伊曼纽尔]]邀请前总统比尔·克林顿向谢斯塔克提出交易，只要他退出竞选，就可以进入总统顾问委员会任职或出任另一行政职务。如果谢斯塔克接受，那么他不但可以继续担任众议员，还可以在白宫任职，只是后一份职务没有薪金。<ref name="Elliott0529">{{cite news | last = Elliott | first = Philip | work = USA Today | date = 2010-05-29 | title = WH had Clinton try to ease Sestak out of PA. race | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/topstories/2010-05-28-622748697_x.htm | accessdate = 2015-10-03 | archive-date = 2015-10-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151006154708/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/topstories/2010-05-28-622748697_x.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Malloy0811">{{cite news | last = Malloy | first = Daniel | title = Clinton draws spotlight at Sestak campaign rally | work = Pittsburgh Post-Gazette | date = 2010-08-11 | accessdate = 2015-10-03 | archivedate = 2010-08-19 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100819013916/http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/10223/1079134-454.stm | deadurl = no | url = http://www.post-gazette.com/state/2010/08/11/Clinton-draws-spotlight-at-Sestak-campaign-rally/stories/201008110271 }}</ref>

鲍尔声称，并没有奥巴马政府以内的任何人员直接同谢斯塔克提及这笔交易，所以也就不存在任何不当、非法或不道德的行为。但国会中的共和党议员有不同看法，他们认为这起事件同奥巴马[[奥巴马2008年美国总统竞选活动|竞选总统期间]]有关道德操守和政府透明度的承诺相抵触。<ref name="Elliott0529" />伊萨甚至认为这起事件堪称“奥巴马的[[水门事件|水门事件]]”，足以启动[[弹劾|弹劾]]程序<ref name="Bendery1108">{{cite news | last = Bendery | first = Jennifer | title = Issa Has No Plans To Investigate Sestak Job Offer | work = Roll Call | date = 2010-11-08 | archivedate = 2015-10-01 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151001015957/http://www.rollcall.com/issues/56_45/-200283-1.html | deadurl = no | url = http://www.rollcall.com/issues/56_45/-200283-1.html | accessdate = 2015-10-03 }}</ref>。尽管如此，事件还是在初选竞选期间逐渐淡出人们的视野，包括政府开销和经济在内的其它多个话题相应接手<ref name="Malloy0811" />。[[2010年美国中期选举|2010年中期选举]]结束后，共和党夺得联邦众议院的主控权，伊萨也成为众议院监督和政府改革委员会主席。有报道预测，由于伊萨之前曾严厉指责这起交易，因此他很可能会在这时对事件发起正式调查<ref>{{cite news | title = GOP May Probe Panthers, Sestak Offer | publisher = WTXF-TV | date = 2010-11-03 | archivedate = 2012-03-10 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120310174225/http://www.myfoxphilly.com/dpp/news/politics/110310-gop-may-probe-panthers-sestak-offer | url = http://www.myfoxphilly.com/dpp/news/politics/110310-gop-may-probe-panthers-sestak-offer | accessdate = 2012-03-10 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>。但是，伊萨实际上却于11月5日宣布他不会发起调查<ref name="Bendery1108" />。部分政界及传媒界人士称，向谢斯塔克提出这一工作邀约即便没有违法，也是令人厌恶的行径，只不过对于任何层级的政客来说，这种交易都很平常<ref name="Cillizza0528">{{cite news |last=Cillizza |first=Chris |title=How the Sestak job offer became a big deal |work=The Washington Post |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130205181452/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/thefix/white-house/how-the-sestak-job-offer-becam.html |date=2010-05-28 |accessdate=2015-10-03 |deadurl=no |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/thefix/white-house/how-the-sestak-job-offer-becam.html |archivedate=2013-02-05 }}</ref><ref name="Kass0530">{{cite news | last = Kass | first = John | title = Sestak affair an embarrassment but no scandal | work = [[芝加哥论坛报|Chicago Tribune]] | date = 2010-05-30 | archivedate = 2015-09-30 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150930155551/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2010-05-30/news/ct-met-kass-0530-20100530_1_joe-sestak-obama-white-house-scandal | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2015-10-03 | url = http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2010-05-30/news/ct-met-kass-0530-20100530_1_joe-sestak-obama-white-house-scandal }}</ref>。《华盛顿邮报》的[[克里斯·西里扎|克里斯·西里扎]]（{{lang|en|Chris Cillizza}}）认为，白宫对媒体反应处理失当，导致事件看起来沦为丑闻<ref name="Cillizza0528" />；《[[芝加哥论坛报|芝加哥论坛报]]》的约翰·卡斯（{{lang|en|John Kass}}）则在报道中写道：“向野心勃勃的年轻政客提供职位邀约，以求保护奴颜婢膝的孱弱老者，这早已不是什么新鲜事。总统们干过，州长们干过，大城市的市长们也都清楚地知道应该怎么干”<ref name="Kass0530" />。

